  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for gawk",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for gawk fixes the following issues:\n\n- CVE-2026-40467: use-after-free vulnerability within the do_getline_redir() routine could lead to a program crash\n  (bsc#1271351).\n- CVE-2026-40468: use-after-free vulnerability in gawk's \"io.c\" file could permit heap metadata manipulation and host\n  memory exhaustion (bsc#1271352).\n- CVE-2026-40553: buffer overflow in the ftype() routine of the readdir extension could trigger a program crash\n  (bsc#1271354).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
